// 5:useEffect
// useEffect is a React Hook that handles side effects (extra work) in a component.
// It is commonly used for data fetching, subscriptions, timers, and browser-related tasks.
// It runs after the component renders and can run on the first render or when specific data changes, depending on the dependency array.
// No array/////////After every render
// [] //////////////Only on first render
// [state]///////// its run when that state change
